    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The Black River Cotton and Woolen Manufacturing Company, built in 1813, sparked the town’s first industrial boom.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.watertown-ny.gov/WatertownHistory"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1849, Walter Hunt of Watertown invented the safety pin, a device still used worldwide.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        30
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.watertown-ny.gov/WatertownHistory"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The city’s Flower Memorial Library, constructed in 1904 as a tribute to Emma Flower Taylor, stands as a historic cultural hub.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        26
